Kerawara is an island in the Duke of York Islands archipelago  in Papua New Guinea. It is  located  in the east of the country, in the East New Britain Province, about  to the east of the Port Moresby.
Geography
The land of Kerawara Island is flat.  The highest point on the island is  above sea level.  It covers  from the north to the south and  from the east to the west. In total island covers about .
